{"info": {"author": "Ryan Morshead", "author_email": "ryan.morshead@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# Slidedown\n\n- Do you \u270d\ufe0f Slides?\n- Do you \ud83d\ude20 PowerPoint?\n- Do you \u2764\ufe0f Markdown?\n\n\n# You're in Luck!\n\nTurn markdown like this:\n\n```\n# Step 1\n\nCreate an awesome slide deck.\n\n# Step 2\n\nPresent it to awesome people.\n\n# Step 3\n\nProfit?\n```\n\nInto slides like this:\n\n<img\n  style=\"outline: 1px solid black\"\n  src=\"https://github.com/rmorshea/slidedown/raw/master/docs/simple-slide-example.gif\"\n/>\n\n# How?\n\n1. Install `slidedown` with `pip`\n\n```bash\npip install slidedown\n```\n\n2. Start presenting your markdown files\n\n```bash\nslidedown README.md\n```\n\n3. Open up your browser\n\n```\nhttp://localhost:5678/client/index.html\n```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/rmorshea/slidedown", "keywords": "slideshow,markdown,idom", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "slidedown", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/slidedown/", "platform": "Linux", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/slidedown/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/rmorshea/slidedown"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/slidedown/0.2.2/", "requires_dist": ["docopt (==0.6.2)", "idom (==0.5.0)", "pygments (==2.3)", "cmarkgfm (==0.4.2)"], "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "summary": "Simple slide decks with Markdown and Python", "version": "0.2.2", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Slidedown</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Do you \u270d\ufe0f Slides?</li>\n<li>Do you \ud83d\ude20 PowerPoint?</li>\n<li>Do you \u2764\ufe0f Markdown?</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>You're in Luck!</h1>\n<p>Turn markdown like this:</p>\n<pre><code># Step 1\n\nCreate an awesome slide deck.\n\n# Step 2\n\nPresent it to awesome people.\n\n# Step 3\n\nProfit?\n</code></pre>\n<p>Into slides like this:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/ce93b51ad25a2fbfe14f384520627bd71d2a39bf/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f726d6f72736865612f736c696465646f776e2f7261772f6d61737465722f646f63732f73696d706c652d736c6964652d6578616d706c652e676966\"></p>\n<h1>How?</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>Install <code>slidedown</code> with <code>pip</code></li>\n</ol>\n<pre>pip install slidedown\n</pre>\n<ol>\n<li>Start presenting your markdown files</li>\n</ol>\n<pre>slidedown README.md\n</pre>\n<ol>\n<li>Open up your browser</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code>http://localhost:5678/client/index.html\n</code></pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 5643002, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "3e31d385476c2071d2f740357ddcddc0", "sha256": "a245f50102caf434a4259a9f2cc4d75595d742a223e2162929a38caf6bd48003"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "slidedown-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "3e31d385476c2071d2f740357ddcddc0", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "size": 92007, "upload_time": "2019-04-19T05:01:09", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-04-19T05:01:09.615622Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/55/22/8230a6ff73566b93567a7e84658f4c3e4f92b3a3ff324506cd71cb44c53c/slidedown-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}], "0.2.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "6e278c8de9dc2d9c79854e7629bd94ca", "sha256": "0e0eaec703fa12fa6500e99ab1d70bb5d406a17a80cf0ee01301cf4fc7723814"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "slidedown-0.2.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "6e278c8de9dc2d9c79854e7629bd94ca", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "size": 26176, "upload_time": "2019-05-27T05:32:17", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-05-27T05:32:17.941782Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/8a/86/b3e5cd9cba1e63f7bf0c4f25